Tailwind Docs: https://tailwindcss.com/
View installation guide. If using React then install using CLI 
If using just HTML then use CDN



https://tailwindcss.com/docs/


margin/padding: 

t = top
b = bottom
l= left
r = right 

x= all horizontal
y= all vertical

if want to apply for all directions, then leave blank. ex. p-4








Responsive Design:

https://tailwindcss.com/docs/responsive-design#overview


example: md: bg-sky-700

this means any size after the breakpoint (768 px) (see docs for breakpoints) then bg color will be sky




example: lg: bg-red-500 
 
this means any size after the breakpoint (1024 px)then bg color will be red




example: md: max-lg: bg-red-500

from md - lg background color will be red     (768px-1024px)





Mobile Design:

Don't use 'sm' for mobile












for React Projects: 

tailwind.config.js is where you define project style theme

ex.

module.exports = {
	theme: {
	    screens: {
		sm: '480px'
		md: '768px'
		lg: '976px'
		xl: '1440px'
}







